    <item>
      <title>2013 Moore Oklahoma tornado path map</title>
      <link>http://vielmetti.github.com/post/2013/2013-05-21-2013-moore-oklahoma-tornado-path-map/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 21 May 2013 14:16:55 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://vielmetti.github.com/post/2013/2013-05-21-2013-moore-oklahoma-tornado-path-map/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This map from the National Weather Service in Norman, Oklahoma (&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.theatlanticcities.com/neighborhoods/2013/05/moore-oklahoma-has-uncanny-history-violent-tornadoes/5655/&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;via Atlantic Cities&lt;/a&gt;) shows the destructive path of the Moore, Oklahoma tornado of 20 May 2013. This is a preliminary map that also shows the track of a 3 May 1999 tornado that followed a very similar path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2a7926970d-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;2013-moore-oklahoma-tornado-path-map&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2a7926970d&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2a7926970d-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;2013-moore-oklahoma-tornado-path-map&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There&amp;#39;s too much graphic, devastating imagery from the scene which I won&amp;#39;t include here. &lt;a href=&#34;http://classic.wunderground.com/blog/JeffMasters/comment.html?entrynum=2413&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;Dr Jeff Masters has an excellent overview of the meteorology of the event&lt;/a&gt;, including accounts of debris being thrown 100 miles in the air to land on Tulsa, Oklahoma.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UPDATE: The &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.nnvl.noaa.gov/MediaDetail2.php?MediaID=1352&amp;amp;MediaTypeID=1&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;National Environmental Visualization Laboratory has this image of radar rotational velocity across the storms&lt;/a&gt; of that day, showing tornadic activity in darker colors. (Credit: NOAA)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2b009e970d-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;1352v1_20130521-Moore_Tornado-Rotation&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2b009e970d&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2b009e970d-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;1352v1_20130521-Moore_Tornado-Rotation&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;UPDATE: The &lt;a href=&#34;http://google.org/crisismap/2013-oklahoma-tornado&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;Google Crisis Map for 2013 Oklahoma tornadoes&lt;/a&gt; includes a track of the tornado plus shelter information and links to other local resources. I&amp;#39;ve included a snapshot from Tuesday evening, May 21, 2013.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef019102647eb2970c-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Google-Moore-Oklahoma-Tornado-path-track-crisis-map&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef019102647eb2970c&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef019102647eb2970c-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Google-Moore-Oklahoma-Tornado-path-track-crisis-map&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;UPDATE: A second National Weather Service map shows the detail of where the tornado was at its maximum intensity. (Credit: National Weather Service, Norman OK, via Facebook)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2deeed970d-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;Nws-moore-tornado-path-outline-ef-5&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2deeed970d&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0192aa2deeed970d-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;Nws-moore-tornado-path-outline-ef-5&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;UPDATE: The &lt;a href=&#34;http://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2013/05/20/us/oklahoma-tornado-map.html&#34; target=&#34;_self&#34;&gt;New York Times has a detailed tornado track map&lt;/a&gt; for the Moore, Oklahoma tornado. I&amp;#39;ve excerpted a piece of it here by way of illustration. Their article also has before and after aerial photos of the damage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
&lt;a class=&#34;asset-img-link&#34; href=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0191026c133d970c-pi&#34;&gt;&lt;img alt=&#34;New-York-Times-Moore-Oklahoma-Tornado-Track-Map-excerpt&#34; class=&#34;asset  asset-image at-xid-6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0191026c133d970c&#34; src=&#34;http://vielmetti.typepad.com/.a/6a00d8341c4f1a53ef0191026c133d970c-600wi&#34; style=&#34;width: 600px; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&#34; title=&#34;New-York-Times-Moore-Oklahoma-Tornado-Track-Map-excerpt&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;#0160;&lt;/p&gt;
